01:41.466 --> 01:44.402
- Where's your mother?
- She ran down
to the supermarket.

01:44.469 --> 01:46.437
When was that?
About 4:00.

01:46.505 --> 01:49.908
That's two hours ago.
Where is she?
I'm hungry here.

01:49.975 --> 01:52.043
Gee, arch, all you can think
about is your stomach.

01:52.111 --> 01:54.212
If ma's so late, how come
you're not worried about her?

01:54.279 --> 01:59.450
Because there's a special
Providence takes care
of drunks and dingbats.

02:00.953 --> 02:04.555
It's only their loved ones
that's gotta suffer
and go hungry.

02:04.623 --> 02:08.526
All right, daddy.
Dinner's on the stove.
I'll get it on the table.

02:08.594 --> 02:12.097
- I'm home.
- Oh, are you, Edith?

02:12.164 --> 02:14.099
What kept you?

02:14.166 --> 02:16.367
Hello, Archie.

02:16.435 --> 02:18.703
[ Archie ]
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

02:18.771 --> 02:22.173
That's all I get,
"hello there, Archie"?
Oh,

02:22.241 --> 02:26.111
I'm sorry, Archie.
Here.
[ Kisses ]

02:26.178 --> 02:28.947
Wait a minute.

02:29.014 --> 02:32.817
What do you call that,
[ Kisses ]
Flyin' through the air?

02:33.886 --> 02:36.821
<i>Why are you late?</i>
<i>Well, actually,</i>

02:36.889 --> 02:41.092
it all started because
you like cling peaches.

02:41.160 --> 02:45.496
- You're late because
I like cling peaches?
- In heavy syrup. Excuse me.

02:45.564 --> 02:49.167
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
There's somethin' funny
goin' on here.

02:49.235 --> 02:51.302
Why were you two hours
at the supermarket?

02:51.370 --> 02:54.906
Well, they're having a sale
at ferguson's market:

02:54.974 --> 02:57.976
Four cents off
the medium size can...

02:58.043 --> 03:00.979
And seven cents off
the large can.
I don't care about the--

03:01.046 --> 03:05.583
and I have the coupons that give
you two cents off every can,
so I could--

03:05.651 --> 03:10.588
Edith, hold it.
You are invadin'
the issue here.

03:13.125 --> 03:15.059
You're hidin'
somethin' from me,

03:15.127 --> 03:18.963
and you ain't gonna move
off this spot till
I find out what it is.

03:19.031 --> 03:21.465
Dinner's
ready, daddy.
Oh, hi, Gloria.

03:21.533 --> 03:24.635
Hi, mom. What took
you so long?
Don't ask me.

03:24.703 --> 03:26.871
Huh?
Here, take this bag
in the kitchen.

03:26.939 --> 03:28.873
Excuse me.
Can't you stand still here?

03:28.941 --> 03:31.342
I just wanna
hang up my coat.

03:31.410 --> 03:33.511
What is the matter
with you, Edith?

03:33.578 --> 03:38.416
Oh, thank you, Gloria,
for getting the dinner on.
You're such a big help.

03:38.483 --> 03:44.155
Thank Michael too.
He helped me set the table.
Oh, thank you, Mike.

03:44.223 --> 03:48.159
That's good practice for
when you have your own home.
Wait a minute.

03:48.227 --> 03:50.995
Nobody eat nothin'
around here...

03:51.063 --> 03:53.664
Till I find out
what went wrong
at the supermarket.

03:53.732 --> 03:58.236
Now, come on. Give.
Well, I knew
you like cling peaches--

03:58.304 --> 04:00.338
I heard that
before, Edith.
In heavy syrup--

04:00.405 --> 04:02.406
yeah. I heard
that too.

04:02.474 --> 04:06.878
I know. Why don't you tell me
how much I've told you so far,

04:06.946 --> 04:09.881
then I'll know
where to begin.

04:09.949 --> 04:12.951
You ain't told me nothin' so far
except "cling peaches,"

04:13.018 --> 04:14.953
which is coming out of my ears.

04:15.020 --> 04:17.488
Now, don't say them
two words no more, huh?

04:17.555 --> 04:21.959
Start your story
after the cling peaches
and get <i>on</i> with it.

04:24.930 --> 04:30.068
Well, Archie, I had
an accident with a car.
<i>What?</i>

04:30.135 --> 04:32.703
Ma, are you
all right?
Did you get hit?

04:32.771 --> 04:36.440
Oh, no.
I didn't get hit.
I hit the car.

04:36.508 --> 04:41.846
But, ma, you don't drive.
Yeah, and even if you do,
we don't have a car.

04:41.914 --> 04:43.848
Edith,

04:43.916 --> 04:45.850
how did you
hit a car?

04:45.918 --> 04:51.356
Well, that's where the--
"hmm, mmm-mmm" come in.
What?

04:56.428 --> 05:00.064
You told me never
to say those two words.

05:01.133 --> 05:03.534
Edith, what are you
trying to tell me,

05:03.602 --> 05:07.405
that you hit a car
with a can of cling peaches?

05:07.472 --> 05:11.609
That's-- that's right.
You see, I was comin'
out of the market...

05:11.676 --> 05:15.246
With my shopping basket
full of "hmm, mmm-mmm,"

05:18.951 --> 05:22.921
and-- and there was Mrs. Duncan
with her new baby.

05:22.988 --> 05:26.925
I took a peek in the carriage,
but I couldn't see
the baby too well.

05:26.992 --> 05:31.062
He was all "swinged" up
with his--
will you get on with the story?

05:31.130 --> 05:34.598
Well, anyway, I knew
I had to say somethin'
nice about the baby,

05:34.666 --> 05:38.736
so I went, "oh, isn't that
a beautiful baby?"

05:38.804 --> 05:43.041
And when I went, "oh,"
the shopping basket
got away from me,

05:43.108 --> 05:48.046
rolled down the hill and
smashed into this parked car
and scratched the Fender.

05:48.113 --> 05:53.351
And then this can
of "hmm, mmm-mmm"...

05:53.419 --> 05:56.287
In heavy syrup...

05:57.456 --> 06:01.960
Jumped out and made
a big dent in the hood.

06:13.738 --> 06:17.241
It was
a freak accident.

06:22.414 --> 06:25.350
What did the owner
of the car have to say?

06:25.417 --> 06:27.885
Nothin'.
Nobody was there.

06:27.953 --> 06:29.887
Nobody was there?

06:29.955 --> 06:31.889
Then you're
in the clear.

06:31.957 --> 06:36.327
After this whole "rigamarole"
here of a story, wherein a man
can get ten heart attacks,

06:36.395 --> 06:38.829
it turns out
she's absolutely
in the clear.

06:38.897 --> 06:44.402
Forget it.
Oh, Archie, I'm so glad
you're not mad.

06:44.470 --> 06:46.404
He's not mad because
he got away with somethin'.

06:46.472 --> 06:50.408
So what if somebody
else's car is damaged?
Archie bunker saved 30 bucks.

06:50.476 --> 06:54.078
Aw, 30 bucks in a pig's sty.
Tell how much you know about it.

06:54.146 --> 06:57.982
Costs you 30 bucks
nowadays to drive your car
into one of them garages.

06:58.050 --> 07:00.751
I'm very glad the guy
didn't know who done it.

07:00.819 --> 07:04.688
Oh, he knows
who done it.

07:06.758 --> 07:10.128
What?
Well, I had to leave
a note on the car...

07:10.195 --> 07:12.763
Sayin' how sorry I was.

07:13.932 --> 07:18.136
Edith, you left your name
on the man's car?

07:18.203 --> 07:23.107
With my address and phone
number.
I don't believe it.
I don't believe it!

07:23.175 --> 07:25.776
That was lovely, ma.
I'm proud of you.
Yeah, me too.

07:25.844 --> 07:27.778
That kind of honesty's
rare these days.

07:27.846 --> 07:31.916
Sure, it's rare.
Because there's about 14 million
people in this country...

07:31.983 --> 07:35.753
To every dingbat
is why it's rare.

07:35.820 --> 07:39.690
Archie, you wouldn't want
some stranger...

07:39.758 --> 07:42.927
To pay for damage
that I caused, would you?

07:42.994 --> 07:45.696
Oh, better him
than me, Edith, huh?

07:45.764 --> 07:48.099
Oh, come on,
arch. Gee. Daddy!
<i>Oh, then don't be...</i>

07:48.167 --> 07:51.469
Givin' me none of that
holier-than-I stuff
over there.

07:51.537 --> 07:55.206
I didn't invent this world.
You wait and you see
how far honesty gets you.

07:55.274 --> 07:57.841
That guy's gonna drive into
one of them tricky garages,

07:57.909 --> 08:01.812
which is so common nowadays
you can practically find 'em
in the yellow pages...

08:01.880 --> 08:03.814
Under "tricky garage,"

08:03.882 --> 08:07.818
and he's gonna turn
her note into a regular
sweepstakes ticket.

08:07.886 --> 08:10.254
Boy, you got some opinion
of mankind.

08:10.322 --> 08:13.857
I ain't knockin' mankind,
but people are somethin' else.

08:13.925 --> 08:17.095
Archie, don't you see?
If everybody felt
the way you do--

08:17.162 --> 08:19.697
everybody <i>does.</i>
<i>I don't.</i>

08:19.764 --> 08:24.635
That's 'cause you're a meathead.
Now, let me ask you somethin'.
You walk into a phone booth.

08:24.703 --> 08:28.372
Suppose you find 30, 40 cents
in the little coin trough there.

08:28.440 --> 08:31.875
What are you gonna do, give it
back to the phone company?

08:31.943 --> 08:34.312
Uh, wait a second.
What does the phone company
got to do with anything?

08:34.379 --> 08:36.313
Come on. Come on.
Answer the question.

08:36.381 --> 08:39.183
I wouldn't give it back
to the phone company.
There. You hear that?

08:39.251 --> 08:42.919
It may not belong
to the phone company.
That's enough.

08:42.988 --> 08:47.158
It could belong to the last
person who used the phone.
Stifle yourself.

08:47.226 --> 08:51.829
I'd try to find them.
Will you
stifle yourself.

08:51.896 --> 08:55.099
<i>[ Telephone rings ]</i>
<i>I'll get it.</i>

08:55.167 --> 08:57.101
Archie, the answer
to your question--

08:57.169 --> 08:59.970
I'm-- I'm ashamed to say it--
is, I'd keep the 40 cents.

09:00.038 --> 09:02.740
Okay. All right.
Case closed.
Oh, no, no.
Not necessarily.

09:02.807 --> 09:06.944
I mean, so you're standing
in a closet and some money comes
out of a wall, so you take it.

09:07.012 --> 09:10.515
I mean, uh, the way we think
of the phone company-- it's not
a-- a person. It's a thing.

09:10.582 --> 09:14.485
Stop the baloney. You said
you'd take the money.
Yeah, but it's still wrong.

09:14.553 --> 09:16.487
I mean, even though it's
a billion-dollar monopoly...

09:16.555 --> 09:18.489
And I'm only taking a few cents,
it's still wrong.

09:18.557 --> 09:21.792
Daddy, it's like cheating
on your income tax,
and that's wrong too.

09:21.860 --> 09:25.296
Listen, little girl,
everybody cheats
on their income tax.

09:25.364 --> 09:30.368
The finest people in the country
do that. The government
expects you to do that.

09:30.435 --> 09:34.038
That's right. Certain people who
are basically honest do certain
dishonest things because...

09:34.105 --> 09:37.675
Everybody does it, and then
pretty soon they wind up
like you, not trustin' anybody.

09:37.742 --> 09:39.910
Leave me eat, huh?
Oh, get off my back.
Well, it's true!

09:39.978 --> 09:44.048
And we're gonna have company.
Wait. Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

09:44.115 --> 09:46.551
Where do you--
what do you mean,
company? Who?

09:46.618 --> 09:49.187
John majeski.

09:49.254 --> 09:54.825
Who is John majeski?
That was him on the phone,
the man whose car I hit.

09:54.893 --> 09:58.329
The man whose car
you hit you invited
over here, Edith?

09:58.397 --> 10:00.331
No. I didn't invite him.

10:00.399 --> 10:05.536
He just was calling
from smitty's garage where he
brought his car in for repairs.

10:05.604 --> 10:08.639
He's gonna have somethin' to eat
and come right over.

10:08.707 --> 10:13.711
Oh, sure he's gonna
come right over, Edith,
to shake us down here.

10:13.778 --> 10:19.684
The dent in his car is hardly
cold, and he's comin' over here
to claim his pound of fish.

10:19.751 --> 10:23.053
How can you know
the guy's not comin' over
with an honest estimate?

10:23.121 --> 10:25.823
Because I know what I know.
I'll show you about
honest estimates right now.

10:25.890 --> 10:30.094
What are you gonna do?
I'm gonna look up
and call smitty's garage.

10:30.161 --> 10:32.296
What for?
Right here. To learn
you somethin'...

10:32.364 --> 10:34.498
About the way of the world
there, meathead.

10:34.566 --> 10:36.500
Here it is.
Hold the book right now.

10:36.568 --> 10:38.502
Now,
[ Clears throat ]

10:38.570 --> 10:41.004
You're such a big expert
on honesty there, huh?
[ Dialing telephone ]

10:41.072 --> 10:45.643
Now, what do you think a dent
and a couple of scratches
oughta cost me, huh?

10:45.711 --> 10:49.347
I dunno. Maybe 30,
40 bucks tops.
Aw, get out of here.

10:49.414 --> 10:52.350
If I'm gonna pay for it,
that guy'll put in for
a whole new paint job.

10:52.417 --> 10:55.720
Dummy up.
[ Clears throat ]
Hello, there?

10:55.787 --> 10:57.722
Smitty's garage? Yeah.

10:57.789 --> 11:01.525
Uh, is John majeski there?

11:01.593 --> 11:03.927
Oh, he just left.

11:03.995 --> 11:07.565
Well, maybe you could help me.
Uh, I'm handling his insurance,

11:07.633 --> 11:10.067
<i>and, um--</i>

11:10.135 --> 11:14.272
and I was wondering
what the estimate
of the damage was.

11:14.339 --> 11:18.075
Oh, would you do that?
That's very sweet of you.

11:19.311 --> 11:21.245
He's goin' away
to look up the bill.

11:21.313 --> 11:24.982
Wait till you see this.
It's gonna be 75 bucks
if it's a penny. Shh.

11:25.049 --> 11:26.984
[ Clears throat ]
Yes?

11:27.051 --> 11:29.219
Yes, I have a pencil handy.

11:29.288 --> 11:31.989
Get out of here!

11:32.056 --> 11:35.993
No, no. Not you.
It was a fly.

11:41.065 --> 11:44.001
Would you repeat
that, please?

11:44.068 --> 11:47.638
Yes. I have the figure.
Thank you very much.

11:47.706 --> 11:50.641
<i>Bye-bye.</i>
<i>Well?</i>

11:50.709 --> 11:53.277
Yeah.
$75, huh?
No.

11:53.345 --> 11:57.080
- I have to admit
that I was wrong.
- Yeah. See?

11:57.148 --> 12:00.451
$197!

12:07.359 --> 12:09.727
$197?

12:09.795 --> 12:13.731
One-nine-seven,
wise guy. So much
for your honest estimate.

12:13.799 --> 12:17.201
How could a can of peaches
cause all that damage?
[ Scoffs ]

12:17.268 --> 12:20.904
Well, maybe it was
the heavy syrup.

12:29.581 --> 12:32.516
Do me a favor and
stifle yourself, huh?

12:32.584 --> 12:36.286
This was all your fault,
like a dope, leavin'
your name there.

12:36.355 --> 12:39.623
- She did the right thing.
- I don't want any sermons
from you, meathead.

12:39.691 --> 12:43.494
All I want is your help
when this guy majeski gets here.
Why me?

12:43.562 --> 12:46.797
Because one polack
feels comfortable
with another one.

12:46.865 --> 12:49.567
First of all,
it's "Polish,"
and second of all,

12:49.634 --> 12:52.903
how do you know
the guy's not, uh,
Russian or Jewish?

12:52.971 --> 12:55.339
Oh, no.
He ain't Jewish.
Well, how do
you know?

12:55.407 --> 13:00.578
Because his name's John.
The hebes don't name their kids
"John." Never.

13:03.014 --> 13:07.351
Maybe he changed
no, no. His name.
Edith, Edith,
they never do.

13:07.419 --> 13:12.523
They only change the last name.
That way they know each other.
You see what I mean?

13:12.591 --> 13:14.525
Two guys are goin'
down the street, right?

13:14.593 --> 13:19.229
One says, "how are you?
My name is Smith, <i>Morris</i> Smith."
See how it works?

13:19.297 --> 13:22.433
Like you got <i>Saul</i> Nelson,
<i>Izzy</i> Watson--

13:22.501 --> 13:24.435
<i>Abe</i> Lincoln.

13:32.110 --> 13:36.046
I didn't know
Lincoln was Jewish.

13:42.821 --> 13:46.490
Don't argue with me,
please, any of youse.

13:46.558 --> 13:50.528
Don't you see we all
gotta stick together here
so we can stop this crook.

13:50.595 --> 13:54.197
Wait a minute. I got an idea.
If this guy's dishonest,
he's gonna lie. And if he lies,

13:54.265 --> 13:57.134
he's gonna get mixed up
and give himself away
and that's how we catch him.

13:57.201 --> 14:00.304
Isn't that exciting?
Once, on <i>Perry Mason--</i>

14:00.371 --> 14:02.706
will you stifle
yourself.

14:02.774 --> 14:04.708
That ain't
gonna work.
Why not?

14:04.776 --> 14:07.411
Because how're we gonna
catch him in a lie?
He tells us one story here,

14:07.479 --> 14:09.413
he goes to court,
he tells another story.

14:09.481 --> 14:12.416
- It's our word against his.
- That was
Perry Mason's problem.

14:12.484 --> 14:14.585
The jewel thief lied,

14:14.653 --> 14:18.989
but della street
had a tape recording
where the thief confessed.

14:19.057 --> 14:22.359
Ma, please.
Hold it.
Don't interrupt your mother.

14:22.427 --> 14:25.095
You was makin' sense there
for a minute, Edith.

14:25.163 --> 14:28.966
Let's hear
the rest of it.
Well, the man lied,

14:29.033 --> 14:33.771
and della street said,
"here is a tape recording
of the whole confession,"

14:33.839 --> 14:35.973
and Perry Mason
jumped up.

14:36.040 --> 14:40.978
That's when he was
playing Perry Mason.
Now he's "ironsides" and...

14:46.485 --> 14:49.419
He don't jump up
no more.

14:53.758 --> 14:56.026
All right, Edith.
That's just fine.

14:56.094 --> 15:00.430
You gave me my idea.
All right, meathead, go up
and get your tape recorder.

15:00.499 --> 15:02.432
What are you gonna do,
start playin'
Attorney General?

15:02.501 --> 15:04.802
Don't argue with me, huh?
Just get the tape recorder.

15:04.870 --> 15:06.837
Are you gonna
tell this man you're
taping his conversation?

15:06.905 --> 15:09.139
Does j. Edgar hoover
tell anybody?

15:09.207 --> 15:13.243
If you don't tell him you're
taping, then you're depriving
him of his civil rights.

15:13.311 --> 15:18.382
He ain't colored. He's Polish!
What's civil rights
got to do with Polish?

15:18.449 --> 15:22.386
<i>Arch, you're violating</i>
<i>his rights under</i>
<i>the first amendment.</i>

15:22.453 --> 15:25.155
Who's side are you
on, anyhow, huh?
Look at me.

15:25.223 --> 15:29.560
I know I got a lot goin'
against me: I'm white, I'm
protestant, I'm hardworkin'.

15:29.628 --> 15:33.230
Can't you find one lousy
amendment to protect me?

15:33.297 --> 15:35.699
<i>[ Door buzzer</i>
<i> </i> <i>sounding ]</i>
<i>There he is now.</i>

15:35.767 --> 15:37.668
Gloria, we'll clear the table.

15:37.736 --> 15:39.670
You get your
tape recorder.
I'll get the door.

15:39.738 --> 15:43.173
No. If you can't do
what I want you to do,
then don't do nothin'. Sit down.

15:43.241 --> 15:45.175
All right.
Youse two, get away
from that table there.

15:45.243 --> 15:48.012
<i>Come over here</i>
<i>and stand here.</i>
<i>Come on!</i>

15:48.079 --> 15:50.814
Get over here. Right there.
Now, youse, stand there!

15:50.882 --> 15:52.816
<i>[ Buzzer ]</i>
<i>Sit down there,</i>

15:52.884 --> 15:55.753
meathead.

15:55.820 --> 15:57.755
Now, I'll answer
the door.

15:57.822 --> 16:00.524
Dummy up there,
meathead.

16:00.592 --> 16:02.927
I'll handle
this here swindler.

16:07.165 --> 16:09.232
Uh, I'm John majeski.

16:22.513 --> 16:24.915
You're kiddin'.

16:24.983 --> 16:28.418
N-no. No. I'm--
I'm father John majeski.

16:30.555 --> 16:32.489
Uh, may--
may I come in?

16:32.557 --> 16:35.258
Yeah, yeah.
Come on in, father.
Sure. Come on.

16:35.326 --> 16:38.395
You can meet the family here.
That's my wife, Edith there.
How do you do?

16:38.463 --> 16:40.998
My daughter,
Gloria here.
Hello.

16:41.066 --> 16:43.634
There's my son-in-law,
Mike stivic over here.

16:43.702 --> 16:47.270
Still want
the tape recorder, arch?
Dummy up, will you?

16:47.338 --> 16:49.272
Well, I'm delighted
to meet you,
Mrs. bunker.

16:49.340 --> 16:53.744
You know, leaving that note
on my car when you really didn't
have to is a Christian act.

16:53.812 --> 16:55.746
Are you a catholic?
No.

16:55.814 --> 16:58.482
Oh. Well, all right.

16:59.918 --> 17:02.853
Uh, may I-- may I sit down?
Yeah. Go ahead.
Sit down.

17:02.921 --> 17:06.723
Sit down there,
father, but don't
sit in the-- oh.

17:06.790 --> 17:08.726
Go on.
You sit down.
[ Sighs ]

17:08.792 --> 17:10.728
Well, that's better.
What a day. What a day.

17:10.795 --> 17:13.396
I-I haven't stopped
for a minute. I've been
on the go all day.

17:13.464 --> 17:17.334
Lately things are beginning to
pile up. You know, Mrs. bunker,
I have a confession to make.

17:17.401 --> 17:21.238
[ Gasps]
I always wanted
to know how that worked.

17:28.012 --> 17:32.382
Uh, what? Oh, I-- oh, I--
"make a con--" oh, that's
very funny. That's very funny.

17:32.450 --> 17:34.384
You have a delicious
sense of humor.

17:34.452 --> 17:39.189
She has a delicious
sense of humor.
Yeah, she's awful funny.

17:39.257 --> 17:42.192
Uh, Mike, uh, may I
have a word or two
with you in private?

17:42.260 --> 17:44.194
Just step
in the kitchen here.
Yeah, sure.

17:44.262 --> 17:47.698
Uh, I suppose you'll excuse us,
father?
Oh, yes, indeed.
Yes, indeed.

17:47.766 --> 17:52.369
"Make a confession." Oh, I say,
I must remember that one. I must
tell that one to the bishop.

17:52.436 --> 17:56.540
That ought to bring a smile
to his face. He hasn't
smiled very much lately,

17:56.607 --> 18:02.312
what with father Donovan
being secretly married
for seven years,

18:02.380 --> 18:06.316
father callan, poor soul,
sitting in jail,

18:06.384 --> 18:09.086
something to do
with leaflets.

18:09.154 --> 18:11.254
What are you doin'?
What is it?
Come here.
Come here.

18:11.322 --> 18:13.256
I think
we're in luck.
What?

18:13.324 --> 18:16.694
This guy is a phony.
How do you know that?

18:16.761 --> 18:18.696
Don't you never
read the papers...

18:18.763 --> 18:23.200
About all them
unflocked priests
runnin' around, huh?

18:23.267 --> 18:29.173
This priest here
ain't kosher,
and he never was.

18:29.240 --> 18:33.376
How do you know?
Did you see the lousy-lookin'
suit he's wearin' there?

18:33.444 --> 18:35.579
So what, arch? Maybe it's
the only suit he owns.

18:35.646 --> 18:38.448
Are you kiddin'?
The catholic church owns
half the property in New York,

18:38.516 --> 18:41.451
including some of your
finest clothing stores.

18:41.519 --> 18:44.621
Arch, if you have any doubts,
why don't you just ask him
for his credentials?

18:44.689 --> 18:47.057
Aw, come on. How the hell
are you gonna do that?
Oh, simple. You just walk up...

18:47.125 --> 18:50.127
To him and say, "father,
can I see your cross?"

18:57.035 --> 18:59.970
Get out of here.
Good-bye.

19:02.073 --> 19:04.274
[ Majeski ]
Yes, well, we have a very
poor parish. We have to make...

19:04.342 --> 19:08.712
Every penny count, what with
the painting and the fixing
and the paperwork.

19:08.780 --> 19:12.783
I-I haven't hardly
time enough for God,
much less my parishioners.

19:12.851 --> 19:16.386
You know, lately, sitting in
the confessional, when I should
be listening with patience...

19:16.454 --> 19:22.226
And understanding, I-I find
myself thinking, "oh, come on.
Come on. Let's get on with it."

19:24.028 --> 19:27.164
Uh, say, uh, [ Clears throat ]
Father there, uh, I'd like
to ask you somethin'.

19:27.232 --> 19:32.770
Uh-- uh, the other night
down at kelcy's bar we was,
uh, discussin' the Bible--

19:32.837 --> 19:36.774
uh, you know, it sometimes
comes up between beers--

19:38.609 --> 19:43.080
and, uh, the boys and me,
we was arguin' about
the words to the, uh,

19:43.148 --> 19:45.082
23rd psalm.

19:45.150 --> 19:47.717
I was wonderin'
if you could help us out
as long as you're here.

19:47.786 --> 19:52.389
Ah, yes. 23rd psalm. Ah, um--
well, I know it so well.

19:52.456 --> 19:54.357
I figured you should.

19:54.425 --> 19:57.394
Uh-h-h-- ah!

19:57.461 --> 19:59.396
No. That's not it.

19:59.463 --> 20:01.398
Uh, 23rd psalm?

20:01.465 --> 20:06.670
- Yeah. Two-three.
- I don't seem to be able to
remember anything these days.

20:06.737 --> 20:10.874
- "The lord is my Shepherd--"
- who asked you?

20:10.942 --> 20:14.644
Oh, well, that's <i>your</i> 23rd.
That's our 22nd.

20:14.712 --> 20:16.880
Oh, yes. "Lord is my Shepherd,"
"shall not want--"
[ Edith ] That's it.

20:16.948 --> 20:20.117
Oh, and, uh, father,
you know, uh, everybody
knows, uh, them words,

20:20.185 --> 20:24.054
but the boys and me
was arguin' about
the Latin words.

20:24.122 --> 20:26.056
Oh. Well, ah-h-h,

20:26.124 --> 20:30.760
[ speaking Latin ]

20:30.829 --> 20:33.763
Uh, have we come to the word
in question, Mr. bunker?

20:33.832 --> 20:35.966
Well, uh--

20:36.034 --> 20:40.470
uh,
[ Latin ]

20:40.538 --> 20:43.473
Yeah.
[ Latin ]
Perfect.

20:46.010 --> 20:51.215
You know, Mrs. bunker, I wish we
could just forget all about--
still think he's not a priest?

20:51.282 --> 20:55.953
Maybe he is a priest, but if
he's still after my 197 bucks,
he's as crooked as the next guy.

20:56.020 --> 20:58.288
Oh, come on.
I'll find out.

20:58.356 --> 21:01.058
I've been forgetting the most
important thing: People.

21:01.125 --> 21:03.793
Uh, say, uh,
[ Clears throat ]
Father there,

21:03.862 --> 21:07.797
uh, not that I want to be
unfriendly or anything
like that, but, uh,

21:07.866 --> 21:10.033
what are you
trying to pull?

21:12.103 --> 21:14.604
Uh, I-I'm afraid
I don't understand.

21:14.672 --> 21:16.974
Yeah. You ought to be
ashamed of yourself, a priest
doin' what you're doin'.

21:17.041 --> 21:19.409
W-what are you
talking about?
Oh, I know. Everybody does it.

21:19.477 --> 21:23.247
Yeah, like, uh,
cheatin' on the phone company,
chiselin' on your income taxes,

21:23.314 --> 21:28.285
but you, a man of the cloth,
hidin' behind your hassock,

21:28.353 --> 21:33.490
comin' here tryin' to
turn a dent in a Fender
into a pot o' gold.

21:33.557 --> 21:36.159
Mr. bunker, do you mean
to imply--
I mean that I ain't makin'...

21:36.227 --> 21:39.229
No donations
to no catholic charities.

21:39.297 --> 21:42.099
Well, the only way
I can answer that, Mr. bunker,
is to quote from the scripture.

21:42.166 --> 21:44.101
"Go from the presence
of the foolish man...

21:44.168 --> 21:46.836
When thou perceivest not
in him the lips of knowledge."

21:46.905 --> 21:51.975
- What does that mean?
- It means, "don't waste your
time arguing with an idiot."

21:58.482 --> 22:02.185
Well, I'll be on my way
just as soon as
you pay the bill.
The bill?

22:02.253 --> 22:06.456
The bill you can send on
to the pope, who's got
more money than God.

22:06.524 --> 22:09.927
- Archie!
- It's a well-known fact.

22:09.994 --> 22:13.596
Let's-- let's not have
any more words about this,
Mr. bunker. I'll, uh,

22:13.664 --> 22:15.598
I'll take care
of it myself.

22:15.666 --> 22:19.702
Father, all that money.
It's not so much money.
It's only $14.

22:19.770 --> 22:22.039
What do you mean
only $14?

22:22.106 --> 22:24.374
Then why did the garage
tell daddy 197?

22:24.442 --> 22:27.444
- Sh-h-hush!
- You called the garage?

22:27.511 --> 22:30.948
Yes. He did,
and they told him
$197.
Yeah.

22:32.050 --> 22:34.617
Oh-h-h. I see what's
been troubling you.

22:34.685 --> 22:38.355
Look. I was having
an engine overhaul
for $183,

22:38.423 --> 22:40.824
the damage your wife
caused was $14,

22:40.891 --> 22:42.826
that's $197.

22:42.893 --> 22:46.596
The parish is so broke
the bishop was going
to pay the 183,

22:46.664 --> 22:50.000
but since you seem...
Unwilling to assume your
responsibilities, Mr. bunker,

22:50.068 --> 22:52.936
I suppose I'll--
I'll have to pay
the rest,

22:53.004 --> 22:54.938
take it out of
my own pocket.

22:55.006 --> 22:56.940
Good night.

22:57.008 --> 23:00.143
Archie, we can afford $14.
Oh, all right. All right.
All right. Leave me alone.

23:00.211 --> 23:02.145
Hey, hey,
father, uh,

23:02.213 --> 23:04.781
uh, I suppose if it's only,
uh, $14, I can make it.

23:04.849 --> 23:06.783
No, no, no. Please--

23:06.851 --> 23:11.488
please, Mr. bunker, I--
I don't want your money.

23:21.399 --> 23:23.333
However,

23:30.808 --> 23:35.445
I'll take that $14 and make
a donation in your name
to catholic charities.

23:36.514 --> 23:38.448
Oh.

23:38.516 --> 23:40.450
Yeah. Well, um,

23:40.518 --> 23:42.785
I only got a five
and a ten here, father.

23:42.853 --> 23:44.787
I've got a dollar.

23:48.826 --> 23:52.262
Good night.
Good night.
[ Edith ]
Good night, father.

23:52.330 --> 23:54.264
Good-bye,
father.
So long.

24:03.141 --> 24:05.808
What's the matter,
daddy? Don't you
feel well?

24:05.876 --> 24:08.545
Oh, he's all right.
Just a little
indigestion.

24:08.612 --> 24:11.114
Comes from eating
his own words.

24:18.122 --> 24:20.290
Here's your
dessert, Archie.

24:20.358 --> 24:22.625
Yeah, all right, Edith.
Leave it there.

24:22.693 --> 24:25.062
What do you got,
anyway?

24:35.139 --> 24:38.575
Oh, a nice big bowl
of "mm-hmm."

24:41.512 --> 24:43.447
Take it away, huh?

24:56.794 --> 24:59.229
I bought 11 cans.

25:21.619 --> 25:26.789
